  "text": "We usually use the term cyborg to refer to an individual who is part human and part machine. Here, I extend the term to refer to human-computer interactions (also see [CITATION_1] . Because our relations with computers are becoming social in many ways, future societies may have to create new mechanisms of regulation and integration-not only for human-human interactions but also for cyborg interactions. What evidence is there that a cyborg society is developing?",
